iwork.patchpanel
Class Intermediary

java.lang.Object
  iwork.patchpanel.Intermediary
public class Intermediary
extends java.lang.Object

The Intermediary class implements the translation mapping service. Any event that is posted to the event heap is a translation candidate. If The translation candidate matches any of the translation criteria, the output list of events are posted to the event heap. The Intermediary process is a centralized service that can be accessed through event based remote procedure calls. The event based RPC functions by the remote application sending an IntermediaryMappingEvent with some expected fields including a "Method" field which indicates which procedure it is trying to activate, as well as parameter fields specific to that method. This RPC mechanism provides an interface to modify or retrieve current translation mappings from remote applications.

handleEvents

public void handleEvents(iwork.eheap2.Event[] e)
Generic event handler. If the event is an RPC event, map it to the appropriate handler. Check the translation map for all valid translations and output the appropriate events. Access is public so that handleEvent() can be called by TimerMan when a timer elapses.

                                       java.lang.String groupName,
                                       java.lang.String varType,
                                       java.lang.String varName,
                                       java.io.Serializable varValue)
Remote Procedure call interface to the setGlobalVariable method of the Intermediary The setGlobalVariable function adds a patch panel variable, or if a variable of the same name already exists, changes the value of the pre-existing variable.

Parameters:
eh - the event heap that the intermediary is connected to
groupName - the name of the program in which the variable exists (to prevent conflicts between similarly-named variables in different programs)
varName - the name of the variable to be added/changed (this should be unique within its program)
varValue - the desired value of the variable
Returns:
0 on success -1 on RPC timeout failure

Remote Procedure call interface to the setTimer method of the Intermediary. The setTimer function adds a patch panel timer, or if a timer of the same name already exists, sets the existing timer to a new delay.

Parameters:
eh - the event heap that the intermediary is connected to
groupName - the name of the program in which the timer exists (to prevent conflicts between similarly-named timer in different programs)
timerName - the name of the timer to be added/changed (this should be unique within its program)
delay - the desired delay of the timer (in milliseconds)
Returns:
0 on success -1 on RPC timeout failure

                                 java.lang.String groupName,
                                 java.lang.String timerName)
Remote Procedure call interface to the cancelTimer method of the Intermediary. The cancelTimer function cancels an already-set patch panel timer.

Parameters:
eh - the event heap that the intermediary is connected to
groupName - the name of the program in which the timer exists (to prevent conflicts between similarly-named timer in different programs)
timerName - the name of the timer to be cancelled (this should be unique within its program)
Returns:
0 on success (named timer exists and was cancelled) -1 on RPC timeout failure, or if named timer does not exist

getMappingRPC

                                Mapping mapping)
Remote Procedure call interface to the getMapping method of the Intermediary. The getMapping method returns the current translation specification for a particular translationCriteria and program. The output list result is placed in the Mapping.eventList property of the input Mapping parameter.

Parameters:
eh - the event heap that the intermediary is connected to
mapping - contains the translationCriteria and program whose mapping should be retrieved. The resulting output event list is placed inside of the Mapping parameter.
Returns:
0 on success -1 on RPC timeout failure

getTranslationRPC

public static int getTranslationRPC(iwork.eheap2.EventHeap eh,
                                    Mapping mapping)
Remote Procedure call interface to the getTranslation method of the Intermediary. The getTranslation method returns the concatenated output list from all matching translation criteria. This method does not evaluate any field equations specified so the equations can be examined. The resulting output list is placed in the Mapping.eventList property of the input Mapping parameter.

Parameters:
eh - the event heap that the intermediary is connected to
mapping - contains the translationCriteria whose mapping should be retrieved. The resulting output event list is placed inside of the Mapping parameter.
Returns:
0 on success -1 on RPC timeout failure

Remote Procedure call interface to the getAllGlobalVariables method of the Intermediary. The getAllGlobalVariables method returns a list of all current variables within the current translation map, formatted as an array list of GlobalVar objects. The resulting output list is placed in the mappings[] input parameter.

Parameters:
eh - the event heap that the intermediary is connected to
